# TaskManager Specification

This document specifies the requirements, features, and design goals for TaskManager.

## Purpose
TaskManager is designed to help users organize, track, and manage assignments or tasks for courses, projects, or personal productivity.

## Requirements
- Store assignments with title, course, due date, priority (1â€“5), and notes
- Persist all assignments to a JSON file (`assignments.json`)
- Allow adding, completing, deleting, and linking assignments
- Prevent self-linking and duplicate links
- List assignments sorted by due date
- Retrieve linked assignment titles and IDs
- Validate priority and due date format
- Provide clear error messages for invalid operations
- Auto-save changes after every operation

## Features
- Assignment management (add, complete, delete)
- Link assignments for dependencies or related tasks
- Markdown notes support for assignments
- Data integrity and error handling
- Unit tests for all major functions
- Export/import assignments (optional)
- Integration with other tools or agents (optional)

## Design Goals
- Simple, intuitive interface for users
- Reliable data storage and recovery
- Extensible for future features and integrations
- Well-documented code and usage instructions

